      "group": "compliance",
      "duration": "2 hrs",
      "preEmail": "Subject: Aptem implementation: Trackers\n\nWe are looking forward to the upcoming session: Trackers. This email sets out what we will cover and who should be in the room.\n\nWho should attend\n\n- Champions and superusers\n- Funding returns and ILR management\n- Funding compliance\n- Operations managers who approve learner changes\n\nSession objectives\n\n- Distinguish standard, custom, automated, and process automation trackers\n- Create, assign, filter, edit, close, and evidence trackers safely\n- Configure process automation availability and permissions without weakening control\n- Explain the main process automation tracker risks and post-processing checks\n\nWhat we will cover\n\n- Tracker purpose: workflow, ownership, and audit trail\n- Tracker grid: search, filters, create, edit, status, history, and evidence\n- Process automation settings and roles: Create, Edit, Pre-Authorise, Process, Manage Tenant Settings\n- Process automation lifecycle: create, review, pre-authorise, process or reject, verify\n- Key process automation scenarios: BIL, RTL, withdrawal, change programme, employer/working conditions, RPL, component aim, completion\n- Troubleshooting: missing tracker types, unchanged records, rejected trackers, ILR exclusion, and created-in-error handling\n\nIf you have any questions before the session, please get in touch.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you.\n\nBest regards,\nThe Aptem Implementation Team",
