      "group": "compliance",
      "duration": "1 hr",
      "preEmail": "Subject: Aptem implementation: Registration, Certification and Assessment\n\nWe are looking forward to the upcoming session: Registration, Certification and Assessment. This email sets out what we will cover and who should be in the room.\n\nWho should attend\n\n- Champions and superusers\n- Curriculum quality assurance\n- Administration\n- MIS/data owners\n- Exams, EPA, or awarding body administration\n\nSession objectives\n\n- Create a qualification in the ILR and add this to the Qualification token\n- Update registration, certification, and assessment data\n- Generate reports on the information and interrogate the data in Aptem\n- Choose a maintainable design for qualification, assessment, EPA, and existing-learner tracking\n\nWhat we will cover\n\n- Operating model: qualification lifecycle record versus assessment attempt/event record\n- Qualification token: qualification setup, internally/externally assessed, assessment level, and existing-learner impact\n- Qualifications grid: search, filters, statuses, registration details, achieved dates, certificates, and postal tracking\n- Assessments grid: qualification/unit/outcome level, statuses, result, grade, attempts, resits, and readiness activity\n- Bulk import/export for qualifications and assessments: permissions, matching rules, validation, and file risks\n- EPA/programme assessment tracking patterns and reporting routes: grid views, CSV, OData, and snapshot limitations\n\nIf you have any questions before the session, please get in touch.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you.\n\nBest regards,\nThe Aptem Implementation Team",
