      "preEmail": "Subject: Aptem implementation: SSO, MFA and MFV\n\nWe are looking forward to the upcoming session: SSO, MFA and MFV. This email sets out what we will cover and who should be in the room.\n\nWho should attend\n\n- Champions and superusers\n- IT management and integrations\n- Security or data protection leads\n- Employer engagement/admin leads where MFV is in scope\n\nSession objectives\n\n- Explain SSO, MFA and MFV in plain language and separate authentication from Aptem permissions\n- Confirm package/contract scope before promising SSO or MFV\n- Understand SAML setup responsibilities between Aptem and the customer Identity Provider team\n- Configure Aptem-side SAML user settings where SSO is enabled\n- Configure MFA tenant options and explain the user registration/authentication journey\n- Explain MFV as employer registration SMS verification and identify mobile-number data requirements\n\nWhat we will cover\n\n- Scope and decision model: who uses SSO, Aptem authentication plus MFA, or employer MFV\n- SSO/SAML: metadata exchange, recognised attributes, SAML Unique ID, user setup and login flow\n- MFA: support enablement, Manage Tenant Settings, internal/external user toggles, email authentication, device registration and reset\n- MFV: support enablement, employer mobile numbers, activation email, verification code flow, retry timing and Classic redirect\n- Troubleshooting: blank SAML Unique ID, SSO versus MFA conflicts, MFA reset, invalid employer mobile numbers\n\nIf you have any questions before the session, please get in touch.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you.\n\nBest regards,\nThe Aptem Implementation Team",
